values: ok. so. i;ll stop being bitter towards chris banks now. hah.
or... maybe he just ditched mr. eelctric? you make the decision. either way, we're out a bassist. we have like two choices. niether of which have equipment. which is lame. fuck. what a pussy.

mr. electric has new recordings up. i would like you all to listen and download them. because. i love them. we're also on soulseek so download it form there as well and put it on any other pirating program you have. we love pirating. uhhhh. the satin hooks have inquired about us playing a show witgh them on august 31st or september 11th. but due to alex's father not letting him play sometimes, we'll have to play the 11th. although i'd really like to play both. well... fuck. i start at memorial on monday.
everytime i look at you i see our infant children growing up.

so many things coming up. recording in lake jackson on wednesday. we plan to screen print many shirts soon using leah's design. we're playing three shows within the next four weeks. august 11th. w/ bring back the guns at southmore house. august 27th at fanelli's in victoria with the alcoholic helltones and september 2nd at fat cats with heist at hand.





annndddd. we're trying to hook up another show on the 21st. if it works out the way i want, then it will be... the crypts, batmen!, doctor doctor, and once again, our respected elders inthe alcoholic helltones. and of course us. mr. fucking electric. oh yea, i almost died tonight. nixbnsunds.

so. mr electric did fucking incredible tonight. leah will post the pictures. <lj user="stickyxasxlips">.

we went the fuck off. uhm. we now need to strat booking again. damnit. so. we've decided we are not playing with two of the bands we were supposed to play wuth tonight ever again. we're starting a new chapter.

october 22nd. indian jewelry, skullening. we're getting booked. i swear to god.
why am i so fucking jealous?

so. shows the last two nights, and now a night with absolutely nothing to do. i can not wait until thursday, the show should be well worth anyone's five dollars. and the southmorehouse is rad anyways. so it's guarenteed to be good. last night was like a nightmare. but it ended alright i guess. heist at hand was fucking off the hook. patterns in movement were actually really good, and the satin hooks did wonderfully. i didn't get to see their set though. but i could hear it from outside. i think i am going to book a show with heist at hand soon. so be on the look out for a post concerning it. the fight pretty show was shut down by the authorities before mr. electreic was able to play. but doctor, doctor and business lady played, and i was happy to see them both. but. holy fuck. business lady was a scene from the most gutwrenching horror movie. it was incredible. we're going to tour with them. i swear. i miss going downtown constantly these days. and chai tea at deidrichs, and making fun of all of the complete faggots there. i don't miss number's. i haven't been in around... two months probably. uh. i miss katz.
so. i finally have a computer again.

show tonight at los compadres, with fight pretty.

tomorrow with heist at hand, at... tamina hall??? in the woodlands.

and next thursday (august fourth) with all of our friends.

mr. electric shirts. five dollars. comment back with size(YL,S,M,L,XL), color preference(like green, pink, black, or white), color preference for octopus... and... i don't know what colors of paints we have.

uh. comment back.

million shows lined up!!! july 31st. los compadres. opening for ten crowns and fight pretty. august 1st. woodlands??? opening for heist at hand. august 4th. fucking heckfest. southmore house the best fucking venue in houston. w/ all of our friends. who knows what's next!!! mr. electric will be known throughout houston in the next six months. !!! and brett might record for us. if we decide he is the best candidate.
so. why do i get pissed off so easily?

i don't think i explained enough last entry. i want to be more ellaborate about the way tonight made me feel.  
imagine feeling something real. something tangible, something you know isn't going to turn away, or just abruptly end. simply imagine. it's almost spiritual. it is something deeper than anything i have ever known.

imagine driving in a car, far away from all stress, listening to your favorite song full blast with the scent of evergreen in every breath you inhale. 

thinking about it is similar to staring at the ocean and wondering why something so seemingly endless exists.

i love this. and at ten am tomorrow i will still love this. and everyday from seven months ago to foevere i will love this.

i love the past seven months. tonight was beauty. beauuutttyyyyy.

i loveeeee you.

ten crowns. fight pretty. mr. electric. los compadres. come.
